    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Internal and External Incident Communications"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "During a production incident, communication failures cause as much damage as the technical failure itself. Engineers who don't know the incident scope make uninformed decisions. Customers who receive no status updates flood support channels, compounding the load. Stakeholders who are surprised by downtime lose confidence in the team. Internal and external incident communications are the formal discipline that prevents these cascading failures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Concept"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Internal and external communications serve different audiences with different needs, but they must remain consistent in the facts they convey. Internal updates inform responders and stakeholders about technical state, decisions, and next steps. External updates tell customers what they can and cannot do, and when they should expect resolution. The two tracks must never contradict each other\u2014a mismatch between what the war room says and what the status page says destroys trust on both sides."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The communication authority chain: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The IC authorizes all communication, the Comms Lead drafts and sends it, and Legal reviews any external message that involves data exposure, safety incidents, or regulatory implications."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Architecture: Dual-Track Communication Flow"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Incident communication flow showing IC directing internal and external tracks",
          "title": "Dual-Track Incident Communication Architecture"
        }
      },
