      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Internal Update Template"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "=== INC UPDATE [{HH:MM} UTC] ===\nIncident: {ticket-id} | SEV-{N} | Duration: {X} min\n\nSTATUS: Investigating | Mitigating | Resolved\n\nIMPACT: {what users cannot do, % affected, geographic scope}\n\nROOT CAUSE: {confirmed / suspected / unknown}\n{one sentence if known}\n\nACTIONS IN PROGRESS:\n- {SME name}: {what they are doing}\n- {SME name}: {what they are doing}\n\nNEXT UPDATE: {HH:MM} UTC or on state change\n\nIC: {name} | War Room: {link}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "External Communication"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "External communications are the public face of the incident. They tell customers what is happening without revealing internal architecture, speculation, or root cause before it is confirmed. They must be accurate, timely, and calibrated\u2014overpromising on ETA or understating impact makes subsequent updates look like failures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Status Page Update Protocol"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Declare immediately on SEV-1."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Post a status page 'Investigating' entry within 5 minutes of incident declaration, even with no root cause. 'We are aware of an issue affecting X and are investigating' is better than silence."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Update on cadence, not on events."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Post every 15 minutes for SEV-1, even if the update is 'no new information\u2014investigation ongoing.' Cadenced updates signal that the team is actively engaged."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Do not speculate on root cause."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " If root cause is not confirmed, say 'We are investigating the root cause' not 'We believe the cause is X.'"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Be precise about scope."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " 'Some users' is less useful than 'Users in the US-East region' or 'Users accessing the API via SDK version 3.x.'"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Post a resolution update with a follow-up commitment."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The final message must state: resolution time, a brief description of what happened, and when the postmortem will be published."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Status Page Templates"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "--- INVESTIGATING ---\nTitle: Elevated Error Rates \u2014 LLM API\nBody:\nWe are currently investigating elevated error rates for requests to our LLM API.\nUsers may experience failed responses or increased latency.\nWe will provide an update within 15 minutes.\n\n--- IDENTIFIED ---\nTitle: LLM API Degradation \u2014 Identified\nBody:\nWe have identified the issue: increased latency originating from an upstream\nmodel provider. We are working on routing traffic to an alternate endpoint.\nEstimated resolution: 30-45 minutes. Next update in 15 minutes.\n\n--- MONITORING ---\nTitle: LLM API Recovery \u2014 Monitoring\nBody:\nThe fix has been applied. Error rates have returned to normal levels.\nWe are monitoring to confirm full stability before declaring resolution.\nAffected period: {HH:MM}\u2013{HH:MM} UTC.\n\n--- RESOLVED ---\nTitle: LLM API Incident \u2014 Resolved\nBody:\nThis incident has been resolved. Service operated normally from {HH:MM} UTC.\nWe are conducting a full postmortem and will share our findings within 5\nbusiness days at {postmortem-url}. We apologize for the disruption."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Communication Automation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Manual posting to multiple channels during a live incident introduces errors and delays. A comms bot that bridges the incident management system (PagerDuty, Opsgenie) with the communication channels reduces these failure points:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nclass IncidentStatus(Enum):\n    INVESTIGATING = 'investigating'\n    IDENTIFIED = 'identified'\n    MONITORING = 'monitoring'\n    RESOLVED = 'resolved'\n\n@dataclass\nclass IncidentUpdate:\n    incident_id: str\n    severity: int\n    status: IncidentStatus\n    impact: str\n    action: str\n    eta_minutes: Optional[int] = None\n    root_cause: Optional[str] = None\n\n    def internal_message(self) -> str:\n        now = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime('%H:%M UTC')\n        eta_str = f'ETA: {self.eta_minutes} min' if self.eta_minutes else 'ETA: Unknown'\n        rc_str = self.root_cause or 'Under investigation'\n        return (\n            f'*INC UPDATE [{now}]*\\n'\n            f'Incident: {self.incident_id} | SEV-{self.severity}\\n'\n            f'Status: {self.status.value.upper()}\\n'\n            f'Impact: {self.impact}\\n'\n            f'Root Cause: {rc_str}\\n'\n            f'{eta_str}\\n'\n            f'Action: {self.action}'\n        )\n\n    def external_message(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Safe for public status page; no internal detail.\"\"\"\n        if self.status == IncidentStatus.INVESTIGATING:\n            return (\n                f'We are investigating an issue affecting {self.impact}. '\n                f'Next update in 15 minutes.'\n            )\n        elif self.status == IncidentStatus.IDENTIFIED:\n            eta_str = f'Estimated resolution: {self.eta_minutes} minutes.' if self.eta_minutes else ''\n            return (\n                f'We have identified the issue affecting {self.impact}. '\n                f'{self.action} {eta_str} Next update in 15 minutes.'\n            )\n        elif self.status == IncidentStatus.RESOLVED:\n            return (\n                f'This incident has been resolved. '\n                f'Impact: {self.impact}. '\n                f'Postmortem will be published within 5 business days.'\n            )\n        return f'Status: {self.status.value}. {self.impact}. {self.action}'\n\n\ndef broadcast_update(update: IncidentUpdate, slack_client, statuspage_client) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Send internal and external updates in parallel.\"\"\"\n    # Internal: war room channel + leadership channel\n    slack_client.chat_postMessage(\n        channel=f'#inc-sev{update.severity}',\n        text=update.internal_message()\n    )\n    slack_client.chat_postMessage(\n        channel='#incidents-leadership',\n        text=update.internal_message()\n    )\n    # External: only for SEV-1 and SEV-2\n    if update.severity <= 2:\n        statuspage_client.post_update(\n            incident_id=update.incident_id,\n            status=update.status.value,\n            body=update.external_message()\n        )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Legal and Compliance Gates"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Not all external communications go through the comms-lead-to-status-page pipeline. Certain incident types require legal review before any public statement:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Data breach or exposure."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " GDPR, CCPA, and HIPAA require specific notification timelines and content. No public statement until legal reviews the draft."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Harmful AI outputs."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " If a GenAI system generated content that harmed users, communications must be reviewed by legal and the trust & safety team before publication."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Third-party liability."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " When root cause involves a vendor (LLM provider, cloud provider), legal must review any external statement that might assign blame or waive claims."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "SLA breach notification."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " If the incident triggers a contractual SLA breach, customer notification must follow the contract terms and legal review."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GenAI-Specific Communication Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Avoid describing AI behavior in vague terms."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " 'The AI is acting unexpectedly' is not useful. External communications should describe observable impact: 'Users received responses that did not match their requests' or 'The API returned error code 500 for 12% of completions.'"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Do not comment on model behavior in external updates."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Describing internal model behavior, prompt templates, or guardrail mechanisms in public status updates exposes IP and can create security vulnerabilities."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Support team needs example prompts."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " When the incident involves output quality degradation, give the support team example inputs and outputs they can use to validate customer reports. This requires an internal update separate from external comms."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Communication Runbook"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# incident-comms-runbook.yaml\ncommunication_protocol:\n  internal:\n    war_room_channel: '#inc-sev{N}-{date}-{slug}'\n    leadership_channel: '#incidents-leadership'\n    support_channel: '#support-incident-updates'\n    cadence_sev1_min: 10\n    cadence_sev2_min: 20\n\n  external:\n    status_page: statuspage.company.com\n    email_list: incident-notifications@company.com\n    cadence_sev1_min: 15\n    cadence_sev2_min: 30\n    requires_legal_review:\n      - data_exposure\n      - safety_incident\n      - sla_breach\n      - third_party_liability\n\n  resolution:\n    final_update_required: true\n    postmortem_commitment: '5 business days'\n    internal_debrief: '24 hours after close'\n\n  ownership:\n    draft: comms_lead\n    approve: ic\n    legal_review: legal_on_call (for flagged types)\n    send: comms_lead"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Failure Modes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Silent incidents."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " No status page update until resolution. Customers escalate through support, social media, and news. The delay in the first update is the most damaging."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ETA inflation."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Giving optimistic ETAs on external updates creates a cascade of missed promises. Better to say 'under investigation\u2014no ETA yet' than '30 minutes' when the root cause is unknown."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "IC writing comms."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The IC must not be drafting updates while also running the bridge call and tracking action items. A separate Comms Lead is mandatory for SEV-1."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Inconsistent internal/external messaging."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " If the war room says 'all users affected' and the status page says 'some users affected,' customers who see both lose confidence. Both tracks must use the same scope language."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Separate the drafting role from the commanding role. The Comms Lead owns the drafts; the IC approves and authorizes. Never let the IC dual-role as comms during a SEV-1."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Post externally on cadence, not on resolution. Customers need to know the team is actively working, even before there is anything new to report."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Calibrate language to certainty. Do not claim a root cause externally until it is confirmed internally. 'Under investigation' is always accurate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gate sensitive communications through legal. Data exposure, safety incidents, and SLA breaches require legal review before any external message is sent."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}